German States’ Deficit Shrinks in First Half, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-08-03T05:31:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/german-states-deficit-shrinks-in-first-half-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany ’s states halved their budget
deficits in the first half of the year,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing calculations by the federal  Finance Ministry .  The shortfalls amounted to 4.7 billion euros ($6.68
billion), down from 10.5 billion euros in the first six months
of 2010, the newspaper said. Five states recorded a budget
surplus, Handelsblatt reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  